body:
Why is `defaultValue` attr commented out?

```js
<input
  name={`test[${index}].name`}
  // defaultValue={`${item.name}`}
  ref={register}
/>
```

It works correctly if you remove uncomment the line.

```js
<input
  name={`test[${index}].name`}
  defaultValue={`${item.name}`}
  ref={register}
/>
```

@bluebill1049 Thanks for the update and the explanation.  I'm OK with using `defaultValue` as a way to get this to work, however I can't imagine a real-world scenario where the default behavior seems desired.  Removing an item completely clears the array inputs.   It doesn't reset back to the `defaultValues` at the form level. 

To be sure I'm understanding you, [this behavior](https://streamable.com/eq71w) is the expected behavior if you don't set `defaultValue` on the input?  It's 100% possible I'm misunderstanding [your previous comment](https://github.com/react-hook-form/react-hook-form/issues/892#issuecomment-577991119). If an end-user is entering a list of 10 items, and decides to remove one, _all_ values will be cleared. 

P.S. Feel free to close this and move on if you consider this working as expected.  I have a sufficient workaround.  üëç

